                            <container
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545825687,1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-23T13:55:15.730-05:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-23T13:55:48.814-05:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="schafsm"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <text
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-23T13:56:19.252-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-02-01T17:27:25.680-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;Incredible new features in the Family Commons include:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>New pre-K to high school classroom spaces, including a science lab and library&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Reading alcoves, resting nooks, recording studio and maker space&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Art room with a balloon-like ceiling that illuminates in different colors&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Indoor and outdoor play areas&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Private rooms for families to rest or relax in between appointments at the hospital&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Cafe with coffee and snacks for patient families to reconnect and recharge&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Stained-glass–adorned sacred space offering a quiet place for reflection, prayer and meditation&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Centralized patient and housing services to meet the unique needs of families&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Event space for meetings of the patient and family advisory council and parent classes&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Parent-to-parent mentor meeting space, tech support center, and childcare&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-02-01T17:24:58.763-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-02-01T17:24:58.763-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-23T13:58:06.565-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:49:08.761-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Incorporating patient voices in the design approach "
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text_652488724
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-23T13:58:37.075-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-02-01T17:26:15.093-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>From the music room to the sacred space, every room of the Family Commons was developed with intention, considering what would be most impactful to patients and families and make their journey a little easier.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“AbbVie has been an incredible partner in that they've been with us every step of the way, &amp;nbsp;making sure that all the details are appropriate and that they're going to meet the needs of our patients and their families,” says Richard C. Shadyac Jr., the president and CEO of ALSAC, the fundraising and awareness organization for St. Jude.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>To ensure patients’ needs were reflected, partners worked closely with the St. Jude Patient Family Advisory Council (PFAC), a voluntary advisory group that includes family members of current and former patients. Council members were engaged from the start, giving feedback on renderings, colors, fixtures and more, says Janice English, director of the Patient and Family Experience Office, St. Jude.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“We even went so far as to bring in some of the furniture pieces to patient families and had family members sit in them and give us input on what was comfortable and what was not,” she says.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Patient families provided feedback not only on appearance and comfort but also on how well features would support the specialized needs of their children, some of whom are immunocompromised, visually impaired or in a wheelchair.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“As a cancer patient mom, one of my biggest concerns was infection protection. I wanted to know that the materials and furniture I would sit on would to be safe for my immunocompromised child,” said Elsener, a member and former chair of the St. Jude PFAC.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
